# Product Ranking Service

REST service that ranks products by a weighted sum of criteria (sales units, stock ratio). Java 17, Spring Boot 3, MongoDB, Maven.

## Key references

- Design decisions and rationale: `README.md` and `docs/specs/001-007` (source of truth: domain model, hexagonal architecture, ranking algorithm, REST API, persistence, testing strategy).
- Architecture rules are enforced by ArchUnit in `src/test/java/.../architecture/HexagonalArchitectureTest.java`.

## Commands

```bash
docker compose up -d        # MongoDB (required for the app and integration/E2E tests)
./mvnw spring-boot:run      # run app (seeds dataset on first start)
./mvnw test                 # full test suite (needs Docker for Testcontainers)
```

## Hard constraints

- No Lombok, no Bean Validation annotations, no MapStruct. Plain Java, explicit code.
- Single endpoint: `POST /api/products/ranking`. Errors are `400 {"message": "..."}`.
- When changing behavior or design, keep `README.md` consistent with the code.
